# Frontend Rules

## Component Architecture
- Page files (`app/*/page.tsx`) should be thin orchestrators: fetch data, compose components
- Extract reusable UI into `components/ui/` (Card, Badge, StatCard, etc.)
- Extract domain components into `components/{domain}/` (e.g., `components/household/`)
- Each component file: target <300 lines. If exceeding 400, split immediately.

## Page Size Limits (ENFORCED)
- **Maximum 400 lines per page.tsx** — no exceptions for new pages
- Existing large pages (accounts: 540, landing page: 722) are tracked tech debt — split on touch
- When modifying a large page, extract the section you're changing into a component FIRST

## TypeScript Strictness
- Define explicit interfaces for ALL data structures in `types/{domain}.ts`
- NO `any` type — use `unknown` if type is genuinely unknown, then narrow
- API response types must match the Pydantic models in the corresponding route file
- Export all types through the barrel at `types/api.ts`

## API Client Pattern
- Domain API functions live in `lib/api-{domain}.ts`
- All use `request()` from `lib/api-client.ts` (centralized fetch wrapper)
- Export through barrel at `lib/api.ts`
- Handle errors at the call site — show user-friendly messages, log details

## Styling (Tailwind v4)
- Use design tokens from `globals.css` (brand colors, spacing, radii)
- Financial numbers: always use `font-mono` (JetBrains Mono)
- Headings: use Plus Jakarta Sans via `font-display` class
- Follow BRAND.md color system: Henry Green for CTAs, Warm Gold for milestones only

## State Management
- Server state: fetch in page/layout, pass as props
- Client state: React hooks (`useState`, `useReducer`) — no external state library needed
- Custom hooks in `hooks/` for reusable stateful logic
